        "type": "markdown",
        "id": "2073ce6eb7a4ed91",
        "text": "8. I did a number of experiments at Chapeltown Academy, Sheffield, where my niece had been in the 6th form. \n(a) I offered a course in Business Thinking and made it easy t participate (free, in school hours etc). At the first session 10 kinds turned up. At the second, there were only 3. I asked the 7 why they had given up and they told me that it was difficult and they weren't going to get a qualification that would help them to get into university! By the third session I had only one boy who stuck with it through thick and thin (including getting laughed at by his peers in the common room when he was sitting talking to me!) I asked him why he had continued with me when all his pals had quit. He told me that he could see how he could use this everywhere and that he was quitting chemistry A level to give himself time to develop his skill. That one boy gave me the hope to carry on. \n(b) I also did sessions with the geography students. We explored climate change as a system and discovered the options humanity faces. When asked how they felt about the future scenarios that emerged from their model one boy said he had a different solution. He told us that we could all get on a space ship and escape to another planet. So I asked him what would happen to the new planet if nobody changed their mindset on the journey and he almost shouted that the same thing would happen to that planet. I asked what should we do then? And he said we have to change our mindset and our behavior. This is not dissimilar to [[Do It Naturally]]."
