      "type": "edit",
      "id": "779ed06d2a6132bb",
      "item": {
        "type": "markdown",
        "id": "779ed06d2a6132bb",
        "text": "11. Tina Farr is the head of **St Ebbe's Primary school, Oxford** [https://st-ebbes.oxon.sch.uk/ link] I ran a workshop for her SLT. she decided to use it not to teach the curriculum but to deal with situations as they arose in the school. She told me a story of 2 boys fighting on the playground. She asked them what had happened and why. One boy explained the history and the other agreed. She asked what would be the consequences if this continued and they explained that people would get hurt and others would be disturbed. She asked what should happen next and they said they should be punished! They suggested they wanted to be punished by missing their break the next day as they had spoiled this break for the others. Because they had been so fair she offered them the opportunity to play a game of their choice while they were locked inside!"
      },
      "date": 1699169090146
